.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Flahive, Jean,|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1119722836|title=The canoe maker David Moses Bridges, Passamaquoddy birch bark artisan / Jean Flahive and Donald Soctomah; illustrated by Mari Dieumegard.|others=Donald, Soctomah,, Mari, Dieumegard,|isbn=978-1-63381-171-3|location=Thomaston, Me.|oclc=1119722836}}</ref>\n\nA scholarship has been named after Bridges, the David Moses Bridges Scholarship<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpeoplesfund.org/news/rembembering-david-moses-bridges|title=REMEMBERING DAVID MOSES BRIDGES|website=First Peoples Fund|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-03}}</ref>, which is granted by the First Peoples Fund.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpeoplesfund.org/news/rembembering-david-moses-bridges|title=REMEMBERING DAVID MOSES BRIDGES|website=First Peoples Fund|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> David Moses Bridges scholarship was provided though the Main Community Foundation that supports the First People Fund Cultural<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpeoplesfund.org/news/rembembering-david-moses-bridges|title=REMEMBERING DAVID MOSES BRIDGES|website=First Peoples Fund|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-03}}</ref>. \n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{officialwebsite|https://davidmosesbridges.com}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bridges, David Moses}}\n[[Category:Native American people]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "Section heading change: Birchbark Box \u2192 Birchbark box using ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Moses_Bridges"}
